PASSENGER INFORMATION
BAGGAGE — Forty (40) pounds of baggage may be
LIMOUSINE SERVICE — P.A.L. has arranged for ground
carried free on each full fare ticket.
Baggage includes
transportation at reasonable rates between airports and
suitcases, briefcases and packages, whether carried in cabin
convenient downtown points in each city.

Excess valuation must be declared in advance and an

MEALS — Due to short duration of flights, only snacks,
coffee and soft drinks will be served aloft.
CANCELLATIONS BY PACIFIC AIR LINES — P.A.L. re-
serves the right to cancel bookings when such action is
deemed necessary or advisable.
The passenger's only re-

course shall be recovery of the unused portion of the fare.
CHILDREN
One child under two years and not occupy-
ing a seat will be carried free with each adult passenger.
Children under two years for whom seats are reserved,
and children over two years, will be charged full fare.
Children under twelve years must be accompanied by a
passenger sixteen years of age or over.
REFUNDS — If flight is not completed due to weather
or other conditions and no forwarding transportation is
provided, P.A.L. will issue a refund draft covering the
complete unused
portion of the fare.
RESERVATIONS —
Reservations
must be made in ad-
vance at Pacific Air Lines ticket offices or at authorized
travel agencies.
CREDIT CARDS — Credit Cards are now available upon
application.
Applications should be addressed to executive
office of Pacific Air Lines.
DEPARTURE TIME — Passengers using own cars should
plan to arrive at the airport not later than 20 minutes
before scheduled departure time to weigh in baggage, etc
EQUIPMENT — 21-passenger Douglas DC-3 luxury air-
liners are used on all flights.
PA.L
RESPONSIBILITY FOR DEPARTURES AND ARRIVALS -
P.A.L. will not be responsible for damages due to failure
of its planes to depart or arrive at time stated on time
table, or for errors in latter.
Schedules are subject to
change without notice.
VALIDITY OF TICKETS — Tickets are valid for a period
of four months from the date they are issued.
